      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "rationale": "Mesh convergence study performed with four mesh densities (coarse: 18k elements, medium: 52k, fine: 148k, very fine: 412k). Richardson extrapolation applied to peak contact stress. Grid Convergence Index (GCI) for fine mesh: 1.8%, below the 5% acceptance threshold. Final production mesh uses fine density (148k elements) with local refinement in contact zone (element edge length 0.15 mm). Achieved Gradation 3 reflects systematic GCI-based convergence demonstration with extrapolated solution.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
