      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "rationale": "Quantitative output comparison performed using validation metric U_val per ASME V&V 10.1. Mean absolute percentage error (MAPE) for peak contact stress: 8.3% across all five load cases and five specimens (n=25 comparisons). 95% prediction interval analysis confirms experimental data contained within model uncertainty bounds. Systematic bias of 4.2% on uniformity index characterized and attributed to boundary condition idealization. Achieved Gradation 3 reflects use of formal validation metric with uncertainty-aware comparison rather than simple point comparison.",
