      "rationale": "Primary QoIs (peak contact stress in MPa and stress distribution uniformity index) are directly relevant to the clinical failure mode of concern (polyethylene wear and delamination). Both QoIs are directly measured in validation experiments and directly predicted by the FEA model without surrogate transformation. QoI relevance documented in Credibility Assessment Plan CAP-TKR-2025-001, cross-referenced to clinical evidence linking contact stress to wear rate (Kurtz et al. 2005, Bartel et al. 1986).",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
