      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "rationale": "Validation experiments conducted using the same tibial tray geometry, UHMWPE material lot, and loading protocol as the COU. Specimens represent the target patient population body mass range (65–110 kg). Loading conditions span the ISO 14243-1 gait cycle envelope defined in the operating envelope. Minor differences: cadaveric bone vs. idealized rigid tibial support in some COU simulations — this difference is documented and sensitivity to support stiffness shown to be < 3% on peak contact stress via parametric study.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
