      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "rationale": "Five cadaveric tibial specimens used for validation testing, representing the target geometric and demographic range (tibial plateau width 71–83 mm, body mass 68–108 kg at time of donation). Specimen selection documented per IRB-approved protocol. Geometric characterization by micro-CT (voxel size 0.3 mm) with dimensional report. Sample size justification: power analysis for MAPE < 15% at 80% power with assumed 10% inter-specimen variability requires n ≥ 4; n=5 satisfies this threshold. Material lot traceability maintained for all polyethylene inserts.",
